Source: oml
Section: unknown
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Christoph Dwertmann <christoph.dwertmann@nicta.com.au>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5), libsigar-dev, libxml2-dev, libpcap0.8-dev, libpopt-dev, libsqlite3-dev
Standards-Version: 3.7.2

Package: oml-client
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libsigar, libxml2, libpcap0.8, libpopt0
Description: OML measurement client
 The OML client component is integrated in the application to collect measurements taken or produced by that applications. Dynamically configurable filters analyze the various measurement streams before they are forwarded to the OML Server.

Package: oml-server
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libsqlite3-0, libpopt0, liboml (= ${Source-Version})
Description: OML measurement server
 The OML server component is responsible to collect and store the measurements inside a database. Currently, the sqlite3 library is supported.

Package: liboml-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: liboml (= ${Source-Version})
Description: OML measurement library headers
 A measurement library developed in the context of the OMF Testbed Management Framework. This library allows experimenter to define customizable measurement points inside applications or passive traffic listener using the pcap library.

Package: liboml
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libxml2, libpcap0.8, libpopt0
Description: OML measurement library
 A measurement library developed in the context of the OMF Testbed Management Framework. This library allows experimenter to define customizable measurement points inside applications or passive traffic listener using the pcap library.
